wikipedia_page.main: Edward Cahill (born 1927) is an English former professional rugby league footballer who played in the 1950s. He played at representative level for Great Britain and England  (Heritage № 384) and at club level for Vine Tavern ARLFC (in St. Helens), Liverpool Stanley and Rochdale Hornets as a fullback, i.e. number 1. He coached Salford in the 1963-64 season.
